<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>New info from Geoffrey Z on EQ PvP</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?TheBlack[BCK]">TheBlack[BCK]</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 7:31 p.m. 24/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> New info from Geoffrey Z on EQ PvP<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR></STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>Oh. There is a TINY (like 1-2% out of 100) bonus added on for

<BR>people a level to three above you for resistances. Quite possibly it is the
<BR>fact that they higher level people have better equipment, or have defensive
<BR>spells up on them.
<P>Our system is heavily based on skills. Giving somebody a flaming
<BR>avenger at first level just won't do much to help them - they don't have the
<BR>skill to use it. Level, which sets your skill caps, is very important. A
<BR>6th level guy can probably take out two level 4's. A 30th level guy can
<BR>probably take out two level 24-25's. That is how all the combat equations
<BR>have been written, and how we have balanced game play.
<P>Superior weapons and equipment will help - a level 25 with equipment
<BR>could take out a level 30 if the level 30 was naked, or in poor equipment.
<BR>But two equally-equipped equally-skilled warriors of level 25 and 30? The
<BR>30 would win. Hands down in a one on one fight.
<P>For casters it is a little different - the spells they use make all
<BR>the difference. But yes, the guy 2 levels above you will save a bit better.
<BR>Unless she has a resist fire and you huck a fire bolt at her - then she will
<BR>save a lot better.
<P>Geoffrey C. Zatkin
<P>Arch-Magi of Norrath
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
